<br>
If you, too, are a blademaster or mercenary who is frustrated, disgruntled, or otherwise miffed at the lack of real damage these classes can do, generally caused by the inferiority of the Celtic Dual and Dual Wield lines as both standard damage and lack of useful or damaging styles, and overall lack of identity for the class.<br>
<br>
The sort-of plan is to roll up a Berserker (or supporting class such as Skald or Shaman, but we're not emphasizing these) and basically cause trouble in the battlegrounds. We're positive that the only result can be pure ganking, pwnage, whatever.<br>
<br>
If you don't believe that the berserkers are superior to other light tanks in every way, try one out. Ravager you get at 6 Left Axe, use it often. Atrophy is the followup at level 12. Levelling up to 12? Easiest time I had, naked zerkers can drop orange cons with little trouble.<br>
<br>
The server? Palomides. The guild to join? &lt;D-BaM&gt;. (Disgruntled Blademasters and Mercenaries). Come, join the fun, join the revolt. Storm the battlegrounds and dish out &quot;uber&quot; damage. We're currently levelling up in SI, so get 10s and hop a portal over. When the plight of our classes is finally acknowledged by Mythic, Sanya, or a patch (1.60 D?), we will quietly disappear, with renewed enthusiasm toward playing our beloved classes.<br>
<br>
Malcontent Blademaster<br>
&lt;D-BaM&gt;<br>
Berserker of Palomides<br>
